20.	What are terminal operations?
•	Terminal operations produce a result or a side effect and mark the end of the stream processing. 
•	Once a terminal operation is invoked, the stream is considered consumed and can no longer be used. 
•	Examples include:
•	forEach,toarray,Reduce collect,count,anymatch,allmatch,noneMatch,findFirst,FindAny.

