Overloading (COMPILE TIME POLYMORPHISM)
===============
Method overloading is a form of compile-time polymorphism where multiple methods share the same name but differ in parameters (type, number, or order).
public class Calculator {
    // Overloaded method to add two integers
    public int add(int a, int b) {
        return a + b;
    }

    // Overloaded method to add three integers
    public int add(int a, int b, int c) {
        return a + b + c;
    }
class PaymentService {

    // Method 1: Pay using cash
    void makePayment(double amount) {
        System.out.println("Paid " + amount + " using cash.");
    }

    // Method 2: Pay using credit card
    void makePayment(double amount, String cardNumber) {
        System.out.println("Paid " + amount + " using card: " + cardNumber);
    }

    // Method 3: Pay using UPI
    void makePayment(String upiId, double amount) {
        System.out.println("Paid " + amount + " using UPI ID: " + upiId);
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        PaymentService payment = new PaymentService();

        payment.makePayment(500.0);                        // cash
        payment.makePayment(1200.0, "1234-XXXX-5678");     // card
        payment.makePayment("user@upi", 300.0);            // UPI
    }
}

Overriding(RUNTIME POLYMORPHISM)
==============
If methdo names and arguments must be matched  i.e method signature must be matched is called overriding.
 This occurs when a subclass provides a specific implementation of a method 
that is already defined in its superclass. 
class BankAccount {
    void calculateInterest() {
        System.out.println("Calculating general bank account interest");
    }
}

class SavingsAccount extends BankAccount {
    @Override
    void calculateInterest() {
        System.out.println("Calculating savings account interest at 4%");
    }
}

class CurrentAccount extends BankAccount {
    @Override
    void calculateInterest() {
        System.out.println("Current account has no interest");
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        BankAccount acc;

        acc = new SavingsAccount();
        acc.calculateInterest();  

        acc = new CurrentAccount();
        acc.calculateInterest();  
    }

}
