45.	Explain Spring MVC flow?
Spring MVC follows a structured request–response flow:
✅ Step-by-step Flow:
46.	Client Request
1.	User sends an HTTP request (via browser).
47.	DispatcherServlet (Front Controller)
1.	Receives all incoming requests.
48.	HandlerMapping
1.	Identifies the appropriate controller based on the request URL.
49.	Controller
1.	Processes the request.
2.	Calls business logic (Model/service layer).
50.	Model
1.	Prepares data to be displayed.
51.	Controller returns ModelAndView
1.	Contains: 
1.	Model (data)
2.	View name (UI page)
52.	ViewResolver
1.	Maps logical view name to actual view (JSP, HTML, Thymeleaf).
53.	View Rendering
1.	View displays the data to the user.
54.	Response
1.	Final output sent back to the browser.

•  User sends a request to the server 
•  Request goes to the DispatcherServlet (front controller) 
•  DispatcherServlet forwards request to the appropriate Controller 
•  Controller processes request using Model 
•  Controller returns a ModelAndView 
•  DispatcherServlet resolves the View 
•  Response is sent back to the user

