How it works (States)
A circuit breaker has 3 states:
1. 🟢 Closed State (Normal)
•	Requests go through normally
•	Failures are monitored
________________________________________
2. 🔴 Open State (Failure mode)
•	After repeated failures (threshold exceeded)
•	Circuit “opens”
•	No requests are sent to the failing service
•	Immediate fallback response is returned
________________________________________
3. 🟡 Half-Open State (Recovery check)
•	After a timeout
•	A few test requests are allowed: 
o	✅ If successful → back to Closed
o	❌ If still failing → back to Open

