34.	When NOT to use indexes?
Indexes are helpful but not always beneficial. Avoid them when:
35.	Small tables
→ Full table scan is faster than using an index
36.	Frequent INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE operations
→ Indexes must be updated too, slowing performance
37.	Columns with low selectivity
→ Example: Gender (Male/Female)
→ Index won’t filter much data
38.	Too many indexes on a table
→ Causes overhead in mantenance
39.	Columns frequently modified
→ Index needs constant updates

40.	How do indexes improve performance?
Indexes improve database performance by:
