🔹 Basic Kafka Questions (Very Common)
1. What is Kafka?
Kafka is a distributed event streaming platform that uses a publish-subscribe model to handle real-time data streams with high throughput,
fault tolerance, and scalability.

2. What are the core components of Kafka?
✅ From your notes:
•	Producer
•	Consumer
•	Topic
•	Partition
•	Broker
•	Consumer Group
👉 You can answer like:
Kafka consists of producers that send messages, brokers that store them in topics, and consumers that read them using consumer groups.

3. What is a Topic?
A logical channel where messages are stored and categorized.

4. What is a Partition?
A subdivision of a topic that:
•	Enables parallel processing
•	Maintains ordering within the partition
•	Uses offsets for message tracking

5. What is an Offset?
A unique ID of a message inside a partition.

6. What is a Kafka Broker?
A server that stores and serves data. A Kafka cluster contains multiple brokers.

7. What is a Consumer Group?
•	A group of consumers sharing workload
•	Each partition is consumed by only one consumer in a group

